    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PAA",
      "[-\nPAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS PHOTO\nFIRST OF THE CLIPPER FLEET\nF-10A\nThis Fokker F-0, a wood and fabric tri-motor aircraft, made the first\nregularly scheduled international flight by an American airline when it was\nused on October 28, 1927 to operate Pan American World Airways' first flight\non the 90-mile route from Key West to Havana. In the thirty years since that\ndate Pan American's routes have extended throughout the world and the Clipper\nfleet started by this six-passenger -7 has grown to 142 multi-engined, high-\nF-10 A\nspeed aircraft.\nWRONG\nMISTAN/\n# # # #\nPAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS\n135 East 42nd Street\nNew York 17, New York\nOXford 7-6300\nSASS:"
    ],
